# CIM Forge — line-ending policy.
#
# Surgical XML patches rely on byte-stable line endings (TR-4.3 / FR-4.2).
# CRLF normalization would shift the source offsets we computed at parse
# time, breaking surgical edits after a checkout round-trip. Pin every
# file's line ending to LF for everyone, regardless of their global
# core.autocrlf setting.

* text=auto eol=lf

# CIM XML / RDFS fixtures must be byte-stable.
*.xml binary
*.rdfs binary

# SQLite databases and lock files are binary blobs.
*.sqlite3 binary
*.sqlite3-shm binary
*.sqlite3-wal binary
*.sqlite3-journal binary
pubspec.lock text eol=lf
